-- Apple to Sell IPad in Russia at 46% Premium, Vedomosti Reports
-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 2010-09-29T05:24:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-29/apple-to-sell-ipad-in-russia-at-46-premium-next-month-vedomosti-reports.html
Apple Inc. plans to start selling
its new iPad touchscreen computer in Russia on Oct. 11 via
retailers including M.Video and Mediamarkt, Vedomosti reported.  The devices will retail for as much as 37,000 rubles
($1,220), or 46 percent more than in the U.S., the Moscow-based
newspaper said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov at 
